Zimbabwe's former President Robert Mugabe. Photo: VCGZimbabwe's former leader Robert Mugabe has died at the age of 95, mulitiple sources reported Friday. "It is with the utmost sadness that I announce the passing of Zimbabwe's founding father and former President, Cde Robert Mugabe," tweeted incumbent President of Zimbabwe Emmerson Mnangagwa. It is believed Mugabe had been receiving treatment in a hospital in Singapore since April.Mugabe ruled the Southern African country for nearly four decades until being ousted in 2017. 
